
[1]smear

   SMEAR, v.t.

   1. To overspread with any thing unctuous, viscous or adhesive; to
   besmear; to daub; as, to smear any thing with oil, butter, pitch, &c.

   2. To soil; to contaminate; to pollute; as smeared with infamy.

          SMEAR, n. A fat oily substance; ointment. [Little used.]
